ed_by: Nizar Ibrahim\nsrc/ontology/taxmods/uberon-taxmod-amniote.obo:231173:created_by: Nizar Ibrahim\nsrc/ontology/taxmods/uberon-taxmod-amniote.obo:231183:created_by: Nizar Ibrahim\nsrc/ontology/taxmods/uberon-taxmod-amniote.obo:231194:created_by: Nizar Ibrahim\nsrc/ontology/diffs/def_diffs.rss:6869:<div class=\"zero\"><p class=\"clearR\"><b>OLD</b>: <span class=\"file\">cartilage arranged into tesserae, blocks of calcified cartilage that fit together as tiles on a floor form a mosaic. Found only in chondrichthyans. Reference: A. Peter Klimley. 2013. The Biology of Sharks and Rays. University of Chicago Press<del>. </del></span>\nsrc/ontology/diffs/def_diffs.rss:6870:<br><b>NEW</b>: <span class=\"file\">cartilage arranged into tesserae, blocks of calcified cartilage that fit together as tiles on a floor form a mosaic. Found only in chondrichthyans. Reference: A. Peter Klimley. 2013. The Biology of Sharks and Rays. University of Chicago Press<ins>.</ins></span></p>\nsrc/scripts/ubermacros.el:18029:(defun oa-Raynaud-disease () (interactive \"\") (insert \"MONDO:0008364 ! Raynaud disease\"))\nsrc/scripts/ubermacros.el:92194:(defun oa-syndromic-X-linked-intellectual-disability-Raymond-type () (interactive \"\") (insert \"MONDO:0010427 ! syndromic X-linked intellectual disability Raymond type\"))\nsrc/scripts/ubermacros.el:115958:(defun oj-Raynaud-disease () (interactive \"\") (progn (goto-char 1) (search-forward \"id: MONDO:0008364\" nil nil 1)))\nsrc/scripts/ubermacros.el:190123:(defun oj-syndromic-X-linked-intellectual-disability-Raymond-type () (interactive \"\") (progn (goto-char 1) (search-forward \"id: MONDO:0010427\" nil nil 1)))\nsrc/ontology/imports/local-poro.owl:2038:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"http://www.portol.org/thesaurus\") obo:IAO_0000115 obo:PORO_0000216 \"Ray-like arm that is entirely anaxial.\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/local-wbbt.owl:50510:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"ISBN:0-87969-307-X\") obo:IAO_0000115 obo:WBbt_0004796 \"Ray 2 hypodermal cell, fuses with other ray hypodermal cells to form the tail seam\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/local-wbbt.owl:50618:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"ISBN:0-87969-307-X\") obo:IAO_0000115 obo:WBbt_0004807 \"Ray 1 hypodermal cell, fuses with other ray hypodermal cells to form the tail seam.\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/local-wbbt.owl:69234:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment obo:WBbt_0006941 \"LINKOUT::WORMATLAS::<http://www.wormatlas.org/ver1/maleHandbook/EpithelialMalePartII_Rays.htm>\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/orcidio_import.owl:78:# Individual: <https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5839-6798> (Nizar Ibrahim)\nsrc/ontology/imports/orcidio_import.owl:81:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/source> <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q23769268>) rdfs:label <https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5839-6798> \"Nizar Ibrahim\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/orcidio_import.owl:126:# Individual: <https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8314-2140> (Raymund Stefancsik)\nsrc/ontology/imports/orcidio_import.owl:129:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://purl.org/dc/terms/source> <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q52097457>) rdfs:label <https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8314-2140> \"Raymund Stefancsik\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/local-fbbt.owl:132645:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"FlyBase:FBrf0239335\") Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"doi:10.1101/2020.04.04.024703\") Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"doi:10.7554/eLife.96084.1\") obo:IAO_0000115 obo:FBbt_00047572 \"Descending neuron belonging to the DNa group, having a cell body on the anterior dorsal surface of the brain (Namiki et al., 2018). This neuron does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the lateral accessory lobe, posterior lateral protocerebrum, inferior posterior slope, superior posterior slope, epaulette, gorget, vest, gnathal ganglion, T1 leg neuropil, T2 leg neuropil and T3 leg neuropil (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the intermediate tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024). There is a cluster of up to two of these cells in each hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is involved in the control of rotational movement downstream of odor stimuli (Rayshubskiy et al., 2020).\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/local-fbbt.owl:132676:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"FlyBase:FBrf0239335\") Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"FlyBase:FBrf0248215\") Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"doi:10.1101/2020.04.04.024703\") Annotation(oboInOwl:hasDbXref \"doi:10.7554/eLife.96084.1\") obo:IAO_0000115 obo:FBbt_00047573 \"Descending neuron belonging to the DNa group, having a cell body on the anterior dorsal surface of the brain (Namiki et al., 2018). This neuron does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the lateral accessory lobe, posterior lateral protocerebrum, inferior posterior slope, superior posterior slope, epaulette, gorget, vest, gnathal ganglion, intermediate tectulum, T1 leg neuropil, T2 leg neuropil and T3 leg neuropil (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the intermediate tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is involved in the control of rotational movement downstream of central complex neurons and odor stimuli (Rayshubskiy et al., 2020). It receives input from many other descending neurons (Li et al., 2020; Rayshubskiy et al., 2020).\")\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
